About Parakeet Communities
Soar with the birds and join our communities!
What We're All About
Efficiency (without sacrificing quality for quantity), clean energy and having a clear conscience. We take pride in our communities, and make sure that each individual, and family is taken care of. We're not your typical company -- we work hard, and have a passion for what we do everyday. We come to work not for ourselves, but our community residents that have a need we can fill. We love our communities, and the residents that live in them are what gives us the ability to serve our growing flock.
Parakeets travel in large flocks, and we want our communities, residents, employees, vendors and all other stakeholders to be a “flock” – working together and flying together. Our destination is never ending, as we expand across the country to make Parakeet Communities into a company that provides each and every resident with the best living experience possible.
How Our Residents Feel
Parakeet Community residents gave us their testimonials, and told us how they really feel about how we operate and manage our communities:
Parakeet Communities has been a great place to live. Management takes care of everything in a timely manner. I've lived here 5 years and have zero complaints.
by
Andy Ross
Resident, Apple Creek
Nice and quiet neighborhood. Wonderful tall trees for shade in the summertime. Good access to roads and businesses. School bus service and city transit just out your front door.
by
Jimmy
Resident, Countryside
Small very clean MH & RV Park. Friendly folks. Close to shopping. I've never had any issues living here. Management is easy to work with and lot rent is affordable for my income.
by
Dottie Cameron
Resident, Crystal River
Excellent place, very clean and good community. A good option for people who do not have a great salary. My family likes living here, and we have never had any problems with management. Highly recommended.
by
Jose Raudales
Resident, J Bar J
I've lived here over a year now, and its a nice quiet park for the most part. Great staff in and out of office. Clean pool and laundry facilities. Affordable rates are something I enjoy, and this RV Park has that!
by
Jules Martin
Resident, Lucky Clover
Just bought mobile home in this park and I'm loving it! Lots of nice people here. The manager is nice, and it's nice that I can have my dog "Sugar" here. Definitely recommend this park for anyone that needs affordable rent.
by
Keith Leb
Resident, Palm Spring Esates
Foundational Values: What We're Made Of
Our core values are the foundation of Parakeet Communities. There's nothing in this world that would stop us from giving back to our community residents, what we give to our managers and company teams.
Passion
We believe that people who are passionate about something can change the world for the better. Our team is passionate about helping individuals and families afford housing that meets their needs.
Integrity
It’s up to us to make trustworthy and responsible decisions for our communities that breed a culture like no other. There’s no compromise when it comes to the integrity of our relationships with residents.
Quality
Quality over quantity is our mantra. We prefer to do things right in our communities. Cutting corners costs us our relationships and time. If there’s a need, we want to fill it and do it right the first time.
Our Flock
We all work together to create a sense of community that you can’t get anywhere else. We’re a flock that provides the service, and foundation that we would expect from our own family no matter what.
